cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the application of fully convolutional networks (FCNs) to semantic segmentation of whole slide images (WSIs) in digital pathology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes novel multi-resolution networks, which involve learning and aggregating information at different levels, indicating a focus on machine learning and deep learning techniques. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with image retrieval and analysis, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
